==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nontaxable
<hw>nontaxable</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Not subject to taxation; -- of
goods imported into a country or sold at retail outlets; <as>as, most
laws imposing sales taxes make food <ex>nontaxable</ex></as>. Opposite
of <ant>taxable</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>duty-free</stype>;
<stype>tax-exempt, tax-free</stype>; <stype>unratable</stype>;
<stype>untaxed </stype>] <see>Also See: <er>exempt</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nontechnical</ent>⟦br⟧
